iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Lusaka &ndash; A 24-year-old woman has been arrested in Zambia for allegedly stabbing her 9-month-old baby before dumping it in a pit latrine, a report says.According to Tumfweko, Delphister Mulenga stabbed the toddler with a sharp object before dumping it in the pit latrine. Police said the incident happened late on Sunday at around 17:00 at the suspect&rsquo;s house. The baby's body had since been retrieved.Mulenga was arrested after members of the public got wind of the incident and notified the police.&nbsp;According to Lusaka Time, in 2012, a 15-year-old boy saved a day-old baby after it was dumped into a pit latrine by its mother. The baby weighing 3.4kg, was thrown into an 8-metre-deep pit latrine by its mother in a bid to kill it. The infant was, however, retrieved alive by the "courageous" teenage boy after being lowered into the pit latrine by a rope. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.